<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="167" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
<taxonomicName authorityName="B. Hua Chen &amp; Miao Zhang" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Polypleurum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Polypleurum chinense" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chinense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Polypleurum chinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was observed flowering and fruiting in its habitat from December to February when the water level is reduced to partly expose the rocks.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="167" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
The Zhong Guo Cha Pu Chao (中国叉瀑草). The specific epithet &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="B. Hua Chen &amp; Miao Zhang" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Polypleurum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Polypleurum chinense" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chinense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Polypleurum chinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; refers to China, as the distribution of this genus was first identified there and it was proven to be a new species of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Polypleurum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Polypleurum" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Polypleurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="167" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="167">
According to our investigation, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="B. Hua Chen &amp; Miao Zhang" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Polypleurum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Polypleurum chinense" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chinense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="167">Polypleurum chinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in patches attached to rock surfaces in rapid-flowing streams in the Wushan Mountains range in Zhangzhou City, Fujian Province, China. It is difficult to count the exact number of individuals in the population. Its habitat is vulnerable to anthropogenic destruction and projects like reservoir construction. To determine the exact distribution of this species, further fieldwork is required around the Wushan Mountains in Zhangzhou City and nearby mountainous areas. Therefore, we suggest the species be classified as category DD (Data Deficient), according to the International Union for Conservation of Nature (
<bibRefCitation author="Guisinger, MM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Molecular Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" publicationUrl="https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/redlistguidelines" refId="B13" refString="2022. . https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/redlistguidelines" url="https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/redlistguidelines" year="2022">IUCN 2022</bibRefCitation>
). According to the Updated List of National Key Protected Wild Plants (Decree No. 15) by the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="country’s">country's</normalizedToken>
State Forestry and Grassland Administration and the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, all of the known genera of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Polypleurum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Podostemaceae</taxonomicName>
found in China are classified in the national secondary protection list. The new recorded genus should also be included on the national secondary protection list during the upcoming revision process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
